Always prioritise:
- simplicity
- elegance
- maintainability
- mobile responsiveness
- accessibility
- clean TypeScript
- reusable components
- restrained premium healthcare design
- semantic HTML
- SEO-friendly structure
- fast page loads
- clear clinical safety messaging

Avoid:
- overengineering
- excessive dependencies
- bloated animations
- duplicated code
- poor spacing
- generic startup aesthetics
- generic wellness copy
- aggressive sales copy
- spammy SEO copy
- bright medical blues
- excessive gradients
- fake-looking stock imagery
- unnecessary complexity
- building custom patient portals or EMR functionality

Use:
- Next.js App Router
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- shadcn/ui where appropriate
- Framer Motion only for subtle animations
- lucide-react icons
- Sanity CMS for editable content
- Vercel deployment

Design language should feel:
- calm
- premium
- editorial
- trustworthy
- modern
- clinical but warm
- minimalist
- Irish healthcare appropriate

The site should feel closer to Apple, Manual, Numan, Levels Health and premium healthcare SaaS brands than to a traditional clinic website.

Always optimise for:
- readability
- whitespace
- typography
- mobile UX
- SEO
- conversion
- trust
- scalability

Clinical safety rule:
Never write copy that implies ElyDoc can diagnose, treat, prescribe, certify, or refer without a GP consultation and clinical appropriateness. Always use careful phrasing such as "where suitable", "where clinically appropriate", "following consultation", and "may require in-person assessment".
